@Dan

I've always seen it spelled MOMALA for Mz. Harris. Google it, and even citations directly from her spell it that way.  It wouldn't be a portmanteau if spelled Momele.
Momele is direct from Yiddish.

@Barry Ancona

Very methodical here.  NE, NW, SE, then SW. No jumping between quadrants save for finding the beginning toehold.  

Just barely under my Saturday average.

@Michael Weiland,

That was my last square, as well. 

The blank puzzle looked more intimidating than it actually was. All those white squares! But once I started in, it flowed pretty well, with some speed bumps in each quadrant.

