@Linda Jo
I suspect you won't see this but for some archive solver in 2041:
I think the ghost solves sometimes arise from linguistic 'shapes' that many languages contain. So, in English opening FL- is associated with short quick movements as in FLash, FLicker, FLare, and arguably even FLirt. A closing -MP is associated with slow heavy movements as in traMP, stoMP, claMP, sluMP, thuMP. Guessing one in the category will summon the ghosts of the others.

